# FinTrack Pre-Edit Compliance

Before making any code changes, identify whether the target file belongs to `backend/**` or `frontend/**` and apply the matching rule file.

Mandatory workflow before editing:
- Confirm applicable domain rules (`backend` or `frontend`) and plan changes to satisfy them.
- Refactor the requested change if needed so implementation follows the enforced architecture.
- Reject anti-patterns even if requested directly.

Hard requirements:
- Keep typed method signatures in TypeScript code (params and return types).
- Respect layer boundaries and avoid placing business logic in presentation/controller layers.
- Use existing quality gates before finishing code changes when applicable.
